            <title>[JCR-2371] Core: WEAKREFERENCE properties object have type REFERENCE when being read from the persistent layer</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-2371</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>it seems to me that WEAKREFERENCE properties are properly created and stored as such but are read as REFERENCE &lt;br/&gt;
properties when built again from the persistent layer.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
how to reproduce:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
- create a new WEAKREFERENCE property and save the changes&lt;br/&gt;
- force reading from the persistent layer  (in my case I used Day&amp;#39;s CRX and restartet the server)&lt;br/&gt;
- the former WEAKREFERENCE will now be displayed as REFERENCE.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
